{
  "texts": [
    "These factors have made it essential to embrace the use of IoT technology in agriculture.",
    "However, several challenges come with implementing IoT in this sector.",
    "These challenges include the need for devices to be interoperable to effectively exchange data (Dhal et al. 2024), the high consumption of energy and water required to achieve optimal crop yield, then increased costs and time associated with continuous monitoring (Seetha et al. 2023), the lack of industry standardization, and the implementation costs involved.",
    "Overcoming these challenges is crucial to fully realize the potential benefits of IoT in agriculture, such as improving efficiency, reducing costs, and increasing productivity (Rana et al. 2023).",
    "Table 5, presents an overview of the challenges associated with the implementation of IoT applications in agriculture that have been identified in the literature and discussed in this section."
  ]
}